"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"You've probably never asked this question, because you probably don't know how to value the abundance of information you produce on a daily basis.\\n\\n--\\n\\nWhen companies do their accounting, they call these things \\\"intangible assets\\\". When they onboard employees, they make sure they retain the rights over their IP. When they produce IP, they make sure they don't sign it away easily. This is sensible - because **companies value their content.**\\n\\n--\\n\\nMany terms of service agreements mention the right that you've granted these companies to use your content *in any ways made possible in the future*.\\n\\nTry this thought experiment: take a moment and **imagine what some of those might be.**\\n\\n**remembering that data has an infinite shelf life\\n\\n--\\n\\nThese companies are powered by algorithms, and those algorithms are powered by your content. Without fuel to throw into the furnaces, these engines would stop turning.\\n\\n--\\n\\n\\\"We need to make sure our users never figure out how much their content is worth, otherwise they'll never keep letting us use it for free\\\"\\n\\n-- \\n\\nNow what if you owned your community?\\n\\n--\\n\\nYOU ARE BUILDING THE METAVERSE\\n\\nSO YOU SHOULD OWN IT.\",\"timestamp\":1627709023,\"title\":\"Who Owns Your Content?\",\"publication\":\"m\"},\"digest\":\"WEayZ3Si69499L7bwBcRNXLD9u-CrdAFfXEdVguwJMQ\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0xbfDb50Dc66C8Df9fd9688D8fe5A0C34126427645\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"EFXAL94mxTWM2tEz4pA2uDBtbMcA_7pApqGX3cTq1Q8\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"RREiCqsOwgwoXew50z_-gAjRIP-B0Rx6lqc1HD9kW7c\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"4SU2lGCxsnl42XEBCZKyzs5bNPKPO70c3-ZE6hpQsHmzkhNNeD5GK9Ry1EVQUPYeGgQ0TY89zwRzxnI1Ht3T4w\",\"signingKeySignature\":\"0x24eecf55313ff679633053490f7c6fbd7f4346a6e2bcdfe752423a579007c0b248855e83e76195148100e52aa0d5194d31cf1b0a1689713d722bb0b1fcb9add51b\",\"sign